messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
This is the county with a transfer. I just see the call over. He's at 1127K Parbour Court. The apartment next door has a fire.
A structure on fire? What's the address?
1127K Parbour Court. An apartment building, and one of the apartments is on fire.
Do you know if the fire is put out?
The people that own the apartment used a fire extinguisher to put it out.
So you don't need a fire truck out there?
No, but we weren't sure they were there. We saw smoke from the door. It was coming out of the doors and windows. They said they put it out.
The fire department still needs to go out, okay?
Alright, that's fine.
Complex, there was a fire next door. The fire department and police came, but the guy wouldn't come out, and now he's started shooting.
They are shooting at my door trying to get in.
Are you inside your apartment?
Yes, I'm in number four, 1127 Cape Harbor Court.
Okay, I'm adding that to the notes for the officers. Stay inside, stay safe.
Okay, thank you.
If you need to, we can stay on the line with you until the officers get there.
Someone's knocking at my door.
Do you have a peephole?
Yes, but I'm scared to look. They're still shooting.
Stay on the phone with me. Go to the back of your apartment, away from the door.
I'm in a closet right now.
Okay, I'll stay on the line with you. Have you heard any updates from the officers?
No, they're still trying to secure the area.
I will keep you informed. Let me know if you hear anything.
Thank you. It's just me and my two cats here.
Are your cats safe with you?
Yes, one is with me in the closet, the other is in the bathtub.
They're likely just scared. Can you hear anything now?
No, it's quiet now.
Okay, just stay there for now.
I heard a knock again. Should I open it?
If you feel it's safe, open it carefully. It could be the police.
Okay, I'll check.
Good, let me know as soon as you can.
They said it's safe. Thank you for staying with me.
You're welcome. Stay safe.
